.TH _PRINTF 3 "December 2024" "Custom printf" "Library Functions"
.SH NAME
_printf \- Custom implementation of printf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.sp
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B _printf
is a custom implementation of the standard C library function
.B printf.
It formats and prints data to the standard output (stdout) according to the format string provided.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B format
The format string that specifies how the subsequent arguments are converted for output.
.TP
.B ...
Optional arguments to be formatted and printed according to the format string.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte used to end output to strings), or a negative value if an error occurred.
.SH FORMAT SPECIFIERS
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal '%' character.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
.B #include "main.h"
.sp
.B int main() {
.B     int num = 42;
.B     char *str = "Hello, World!";
.sp
.B     _printf("Character: %c\n", 'A');
.B     _printf("String: %s\n", str);
.B     _printf("Number: %d\n", num);
.B     _printf("Percentage: %%\n");
.B     return 0;
.B }
.fi
.sp
Output:
.sp
.nf
Character: A
String: Hello, World!
Number: 42
Percentage: %
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
printf(3), fprintf(3), sprintf(3)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Giovanni Farias (ginftls)
